modules.description: This module sets up and executes test suites in a browser environment, attaching test runners to document load events and displaying results with optional color output. It operates on `Webtest.Suite.t` structures, which define test cases and assertions. Concrete use cases include running unit tests for client-side OCaml applications compiled with js_of_ocaml and verifying browser-specific functionality during development.

This module enables in-browser testing of OCaml applications compiled with js_of_ocaml by executing test suites defined as `Webtest.Suite.t` structures. It automatically attaches test runners to document load events and displays results, optionally with colored output. Key operations include defining test cases with assertions, running suites, and reporting outcomes directly in the browser. Use it to verify client-side logic and browser-specific behavior during development.
